Actions.Text:
%ExecutingThisMacro%

This macro shows how to use the options "customButtonText" and "customButtonSubmitResultButton".

"customButtonText" causes a button to be displayed with the specified text.

"customButtonSubmitResultButton" indicates that the button should act like a Submit button (OK button). This means the currently selected item is return in sspResult, and sspResultButton contains the value specified in this option.

So... 

customButtonText: Edit
customButtonSubmitResultButton: EditPerson

...shows a button named "Edit". When you select something and click the Edit button, the dialog closes, and sspResultButton contains "EditPerson" and sspResult contains the selected person.
